   Cohen, Ismael},
Title = {Sub-spatial prediction of votes integrating socioeconomic, educational,
   and age strata with machine learning and topological data analysis},
Journal = {JOURNAL OF BIG DATA},
Year = {2025},
Volume = {12},
Number = {1},
Month = {MAR 7},
Abstract = {The problem of election outcome prediction has been widely studied with
   various tools, and in recent years the study has grown considerably with
   methods taking spatial information into account. We present an
   innovative approach by integrating machine learning, topological data
   analysis, and geostatistics to predict voting preferences in the 2021
   gubernatorial election in the Mexican state of Nuevo Le \& oacute;n,
   Mexico. In addition, we propose two classification models to predict
   voter preference, one geospatial and one non-geospatial, which result
   from evaluating multiple models. With these proposed models, we can
   predict the actual winner of that election. The geospatial model allows
   us to explore voting preferences by area, which could be of great
   importance to candidates in their electoral campaigns.},
