   contents of Cr and As exceeded their upper continental crust by 1.5 and
   3.1 times and their maximum acceptable values by 1.5 and 1.5 times. The
   analysis demonstrated the presence of sites where all these elements
   displayed comparatively higher values. The combined application of
   compositional data analysis and geospatial mapping revealed multivariate
   outliers, which were located in structural-metallogenic zones with
   active ore exploitation . The application of unsupervised machine
   learning algorithm unveiled three groups within the main dataset and the
   clr-biplot identified the source-specific elements. Particularly, Group
