   Calcisols were developed and comparatively high Cu contents were
   attributed to agricultural activities and vehicle emissions. Group II is
   represented by the geochemical association of Fe, Co, Cr, Mn, Zn, and
   As. The formation of this group is conditioned by volcanic rocks of the
   local geological origin. However, no spatial pattern was identified in
   Group II distribution aligned with soil types. Group III included Ti, V,
   Pb, and Ba, which may},
